    "Id": "chassisdef_balar_BL1-OB",
    "Name": "Balar",
    "Details": "The <i>Balar</i> was designed by Luthien Armor Works and released alongside the <i>Avatar</i> as a competitor to the Inner Sphere's first OmniMech design. While the <i>Avatar</i> was based upon the clan's <i>Vulture</i> OmniMech, the <i>Balar</i> took cues from the <i>Ebon Jaguar</i> instead. Due to the expense of the 350-rated XL engine, the <i>Balar</i> was overlooked by the DCMS, and went on to be licensed for production by other manufacturers, such as Corean Enterprises, Irian Technologies, and Defiance Industries.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Narrow/Low Profile</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.05</color></b>\n\n<color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limits: Omni</color>",
